data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":350,"item_id":"msg_064082bcb2f630f400693a1d6334848194ad5ad07eb850e26f","output_index":4,"content_index":0,"text":"Do you mean a \"secondary agent\" in a particular context (AI/multi-agent systems, robotics, customer support, pharmacology, real estate, law enforcement, etc.)? The term can mean different things. Here are common meanings and what a secondary agent can do in each:\n\n- AI / multi-agent systems:\n  - Handle specific sub-tasks delegated by a primary agent (data cleaning, preprocessing, monitoring).\n  - Provide redundancy/failover (take over if primary fails).\n  - Run specialized models (e.g., vision or planning) and feed results to the primary.\n  - Monitor environment and alert primary to changes or anomalies.\n  - Act as a mediator/arbitrator in negotiations between agents.\n\n- Robotics / control:\n  - Provide safety supervision and emergency stop.\n  - Perform secondary manipulations or sensing (e.g., a camera drone supporting a ground robot).\n  - Coordinate joint tasks and resolve conflicts.\n\n- Customer support / contact centers:\n  - Serve as escalation or specialist agent for complex issues.\n  - Handle follow-ups, quality checks, or after-hours coverage.\n  - Take over when primary agent is busy or unavailable.\n\n- Healthcare / pharmacology:\n  - Act as an adjuvant drug that boosts efficacy or reduces side effects of the primary drug.\n  - Provide symptomatic relief or prophylaxis alongside the main treatment.\n\n- Security / intelligence:\n  - Act as backup operative, informant, or support asset for the primary agent.\n  - Gather extra intelligence, perform surveillance, or secure logistics.\n\nIf you tell me which domain you mean, I’ll list specific capabilities, examples, and how to design or deploy a secondary agent for that scenario.","logprobs":[]}

